{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 65,
  "title": "第六十五章（玄德）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "故曰："
    },
    {
      "text": "為道者非以明民也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "將以愚之也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "民之難治也，以亓知也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "故："
    },
    {
      "text": "以知知邦，邦之賊也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "以不知知邦，邦之德也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "恆知此兩者，亦稽式也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "恆知稽式，此謂玄德。"
    },
    {
      "text": "玄德深矣，遠矣，與物反矣，乃至大順。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 11,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "說古之善以道治身及治國者，不以道教民明智巧詐也，將以道德教民，使質樸不詐偽。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 11,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "民之所以難治者，以其智多而為巧偽。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 11,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "使智慧之人治國之政事，必遠道德，妄作威福，為國之賊也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 11,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不使智慧之人治國之政事，則民守正直，不為邪飾，上下相親，君臣同力，故為國之福也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 8,
          "start": 10,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "兩者謂智與不智也。常能智者為賊，不智者為福，是治身治國之法式也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 8,
          "start": 10,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "玄，天也。能知治身及治國之法式，是謂與天同德也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "玄德之人深不可測，遠不可及也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 8,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "玄德之人與萬物反異，萬物欲益己，玄德施與人也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 9,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 18
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "玄德與萬物反異，故能至大順。順天理也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 11,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "明謂多見巧詐，蔽其樸也。愚謂無知守真，順自然也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 11,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "多智巧詐，故難治也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 11,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "智，猶治也，以智而治國，所以謂之賊者，故謂之智也。民之難治，以其多智也，當務塞兌閉門，令無知無欲，而以智術動民。邪心既動，復以巧術防民之偽，民知其術，防隨而避之，思惟密巧，奸偽益滋，故曰，以智治國，國之賊也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 8,
          "start": 10,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "稽，同也。今古之所同，則而不可廢，能知稽式，是謂玄德，玄德深矣，遠矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 8,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "反其真也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 9,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 18
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
